title: Personal Finance Management App
description:
This project is a comprehensive offline-first mobile application for personal finance management, developed with Flutter. The application was designed to give users full control over their personal finances without relying on an internet connection. It allows users to track income and expenses, manage multiple financial accounts, plan budgets, and set long-term financial goals while keeping all data securely stored on the device.
The app focuses on providing a clear and structured view of financial activity. Users can record transactions with detailed metadata such as categories, notes, and dates, manage several accounts simultaneously, and automate recurring income or expenses such as salaries or subscriptions. Budgeting and goal-tracking features help users monitor spending limits and visualize progress toward savings targets, making financial planning intuitive and practical.
A strong emphasis was placed on analytics and data visualization. The application includes interactive charts and reports that help users analyze spending patterns over time, compare different periods, and understand category-level expenses. Balance trends, expense distribution, and financial dynamics are presented in a clean and readable format, enabling informed financial decisions without overwhelming the user.
To simplify data management, the app supports multiple input and export options. Users can scan receipts using the device camera, import transaction data automatically from bank SMS notifications, and view activity in a calendar-based interface. Financial data can be exported to CSV or PDF formats for external analysis or record keeping, all while maintaining an offline-first workflow.
Security and user experience were key priorities throughout development. The application includes PIN-based protection and biometric authentication for secure access, supports multiple interface languages, and offers a premium subscription model through in-app purchases. A built-in support system with a chat-based ticket interface ensures users can easily request assistance when needed.
From a technical perspective, the app follows clean architecture principles with a clear separation between data, domain, and presentation layers. State management is handled using the BLoC pattern to ensure predictable behavior, scalability, and testability. A high-performance local database enables fast queries and smooth operation, while careful optimization ensures responsive UI performance and stable animations across different devices.
This project demonstrates the development of a production-ready mobile application that combines robust offline data handling, advanced analytics, strong security practices, and a polished user experience. It reflects a focus on real-world usability, performance, and maintainable architecture in modern cross-platform mobile development.

title: Video Call Application
description:
This project is a modern web-based video conferencing application that I built from scratch. It combines real-time communication capabilities with advanced AI features, making online meetings more productive and user-friendly. The application supports secure video and audio calls, screen sharing, file exchange, and real-time chat in a smooth and responsive interface.
What sets this application apart is its intelligent assistance layer. Using real-time speech recognition and server-side processing, the system automatically transcribes conversations, extracts key action items, and generates concise meeting summaries which can be emailed to participants. I also implemented multi-language support, allowing users to communicate and receive translated subtitles in several major languages.
The technical architecture ensures reliable connectivity for both small and larger group calls. It utilizes a hybrid WebRTC approach: simple peer-to-peer connections for one-on-one communication and a scalable SFU (Selective Forwarding Unit) for group calls, keeping bandwidth optimized while maintaining high quality. To enhance the user experience, I integrated features such as gesture recognition and smart noise suppression using modern web APIs and machine-learning models.
In addition, the app includes built-in scheduling tools with automated reminders, secure room access controls, and persistent preferences like language and theme selection. It was designed with responsive layouts and touch-friendly controls so it works seamlessly across desktops, tablets, and mobile devices without sacrificing performance.
This video call solution not only provides a complete communication platform, but also leverages modern AI and web technologies to enhance productivity and ease of use in real time.
